<br>
I beg to differ, I play a 55 bard on Tarew Marr and I will say this expansion completely sucks for bards. Whereas before luclin any guild that had 4-5 bards could take a bard and put them in each group. And the bard could individually benefit each group and you would build groups around where the bard was and how many you had. We all had a purpose pre Luclin.<br>
<br>
Now Post Luclin you need 1 single 58+ bard (if your under level 58 youre useless) to cover the entire raid for your bard needs. Instead of giving us more use on raids and making us more versatile you now need a single Bard on a raid completly taking away use for bards in guilds. We used to be pretty desirable in Uber guilds as there is a shortage of bards. Now noone wants to be bothered with us.<br>
<br>
Spells: Besides the aforementioned Mistake that is our AE songs, Most of our Luclin spells suck<br>
Level 15 food song:Why the hell do we get a food song? Not only is this song useless but as i write this today the song is accually still broken! Amazing<br>
Level 30 Amplification: A decent song to be sure, but its limitations and lack of really good applications on raids make me not use this till past level 50. This WOULD have made a great song for Targeted resists With our Psalm series of songs+epic stacking+puretone. But unfortunatley due to the AE songs you cant play these Psalm songs becuase they dont stack. Without AE resist songs, this would have made a GRAET song for the group raid bard<br>
Level 39 Kattas song dancing:The dex buff and weapon proc technically should be nice, but any shaman buffs dex better than we can. It just seems thrown in to give bards a dex buff which we were lacking. And without an instrument this songs useless<br>
Level 49 Selos Chorus:Ok, kudos to verant on this one. This is a Great great song, Now we finally have a way to travel quickly through indoor zones. the 2 and a half minute duration is just right for this song. The problem is for the Most part this makes the level 51 travel song uselss. With the level 51 song we got lev speed and invis all in one shot, but the song breaks if you get spotted, leaving you very vulnerable, Now I just proc my SS boots, play this song and cast invis And I have the same effect and I cant get the song dropped for 3 minutes. The level 51 travel song needs to be changed to not drop when your hit and this song will be balanced<br>
<br>
Level 52 battlecry of the Vahshir:This song was nerfed to be group only (yay! Its not AE no more)And it would be a great song except for the fact that its STILL aftre 5 Months Bugged. If you arent wearing a Haste item or you have no haste cast on you, this song will accually SLOW your attacks to nothing. In groups without a chanter thi song is too risky.<br>
<br>
Level 54 56 and 58: AE resist and mana, ive already covered why these songs suck no need to explain again.<br>
<br>
Level 60 Warsong of the Vahshir: Would be good but has the same bug as the level 52 song<br>
<br>
Level 60 Ervaj's lost composition: This song drops where? I rest my case<br>
<br>
AA skills<br>
Singing mastery: would be a GREAT skill for our Psalm resist songs but becuase of the AE resist songs we cant use them<br>
<br>
Instrument Mastery: Cant complain about this skill, if you have an epic its great and can make us Very good soloers. maybe overpowered but I havent been able to try it. If it stacks with drums of the beast, bards can be a force to be reckoned with soloing<br>
<br>
Jam fest:Not bad either, this will make us solo better combined with IM<br>
<br>
Extended notes: Errr since this only affects our group songs id say this is a pretty useless skill as I never have a problem reaching people. Guess it would be ok for people following me when travvelling<br>
<br>
Ambidextery: Gives us a little more melee pop I could see us soloing decent with this combined with IM and epic<br>
<br>
Scribble notes: Useless, a few patches ago we had our mem times doubled so i really dont see how we need this<br>
<br>
