<br>
The level 60 songs <br>
<br>
Warsong of the Vahshir increases melee damage output by roughly 12.5 percent of fully hasted values.  That means a lot to rogues/monks and ensures a bard place in every melee group.<br>
<br>
Ervaj's lost composition.  Now that I have instrument mastery 3, I'm draining about 600 mana a pulse.  That is quite significant.<br>
<br>
Other songs worth mentioning - Amplification - adds 90 percent to vocal songs, stacks with epic.  Doing 55 hps &quot;legal&quot; damage shields to a group before mage/druid/potion stacking is very significant.  <br>
<br>
Doing 58 dps before hitting the autoattack key while soloing is also very significant due to AA skills.<br>
<br>
That AE mana song I sing now does about 35 hps regen AE to the raid with AA skills.<br>
<br>
AE songs take up slots vs. dispelling mobs and ensures that buffs will stay up.<br>
<br>
Yeah, you're right though, this expansion sucked for bards far worse than a &quot;5 percent and 10 percent stackable haste song not breaking cap that requires a brass instrument&quot; like our Velious songs that have the SAME bug that you described.  (if there are melee in your groups that can't break down and spend 3k for an fbss then there's something wrong)<br>
<br>
/sarcasm off<br>
