<br>
Taking five times as long to kill a grimling than a skeleton in the same zone or any mob on other contients when all of them have the same hitpoints and grant the same experience is just a LITTLE screwy, don't you think?<br>
<br>
One thing that is funny to me - did you notice that every positive point that was listed had nothing to do with the content of luclin itself (the zones/quests etc) and just with things that could have been added without requiring expansion zones at all?<br>
<br>
Luclin zones are 100% pure grade A @#%$, there's no nice way of putting it.  EQ Live has a huge task ahead of them to fix things, but they are still led by the same people that produced this junk in the first place and they honestly do not have much to work with.  How exciting can they make a bunch of repeative outdoor zones.  Luclin handed us what, six or eight clones of Lake of ill omen?  Who the hell is it at verant that thinks more guks sebilis and charasis zones is a BAD idea?  <br>
<br>
As a side note, the best new content in the last year is definately the Cazic Thule revamp.  It's better than anything in luclin because it's a dungeon with some uber content, with well tuned risk reward and powerful mobs with a high xp bonus.<br>
<br>
At this point making the timesinks significanly shorter would just piss off the people who already went through them even further.  They don't need to go overboard - only a few SPECIFIC timesinks were overdone.  I mean, you have ssra, where it took a month for the keys to the doors to be put in, another month for the quest for the emperor key to go in, another month for that quest to actually work, and then a month for a mysterous locked door that had no key to be taken away.  But things are working pretty good now - we keyed up our last twenty or so people in under a week.   Ssra is nowhere near as bad for people just entering it as it was for us, that's for damn sure.  Now make the creator as hard as HP/lich and bring all their loot to up to par with ntov please.<br>
<br>
The vex thal key quest is not bad at all EXCEPT for the horribly broken maiden's eye shard - that and acrylia are the only shards that need their drops significantly increased.  The seru encounter is being totally reworked to make the bane weapons actually matter, so we'll see how that goes this week.  The cursed was finally fixed and Emperor Ssra should be next, so as long as they don't screw up and find new ways to break things luclin's uber content should be pretty decent soon. <br>
<br>
The worst problem will be the horridly bad xp zones, which I don't think they can fix. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uparticleboy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>particleboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/7/02 6:00:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23612.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard point of view</span><hr size=1> You only need a mage for three things:<br>
