1. CotH;<br>
2. Focus/resist items; and<br>
3. Mod rods.<br>
<br>
One mage can do all this.  Two is better.  Thats all a guild needs.  Oh you wanted to play one to be a pet class and be useful in a single group?  Sure you can for the first 59 levels but after that watch an enchanter completely invalidate your reason for a single-group presence.  Dire charm anyone?<br>
<br>
This has to be the second best AA in the game (MGB is the best) and the best in single group play.  Its actually quite sickening.  I only realised the true horror of this yesterday when the enchanter gave his pet (a sebilite golem) a silken whip of ensarning and some stun weapon.  That pet was ridiculously powerful.  In the end what did he do?  He broke charm, we killed the pet and he got his weapons back.  This is seriously broken.  Verant stopped necro/mage/SK pets keeping weapons for exactly this reason.<br>
<br>
As for Luclin more generally, the zones I think are really pretty.  They are horribly laggy though.  I couldn't believe how laggy the Twilight Sea was and I have an Athlon 1900+, GF3 Ti500 and a gig of ram FFS.  Thats just stupid.<br>
<br>
Some of the lower level zones are good but they are zerg zones.  They're lower level versions (or equivalents) to the Oasis/LOIO/OT/DL<br>
<br>
High end content is mixed.  Some good, some bad, some completely out of whack.  The sooner they fix Acrylia to stop enchanters/clerics/wizards making 10x the exp anyone else can make the better.<br>
<br>
Ultra high end content seems to be horribly broken (Vex Thal key anyone?) and a complete waste of time.<br>
<br>
Velious is good.  At best Luclin is mediocre.<br>
