*Good newbie zones (Paludial, Netherbian, Echo, Hollowshade)<br>
*Maidens End and Dawnshroud are good zones<br>
*Umbral Plains is a semi-good zone.<br>
*Burrower Worm Ring is good<br>
*Original Acrylia RoF was good (before the uber guilds asked for it to be buffed)<br>
*Wizards made useful<br>
*Nexus ports<br>
<br>
Bad things about Luclin:<br>
*High AC MOBs make many zones suck for melees, so the zones are emtpy<br>
*Zones designed for the level 40-52 have MOBs which are too hard to kill(other than Dawnshroud)<br>
*Lack of compelling content in dungeons (other than the rare bosses)<br>
 - examples: The Deep, Acrylia, Griegs, Akheva, FG<br>
*Lifetap MOBs suck for melees, making some zones useless<br>
 - examples: Tenebrous Mts<br>
*Nexus ports are still too slow.<br>
*Certain items too common (centi swords, Goranga idols, e.g.)<br>
*No druid ports to Luclin.  No ports within Luclin<br>
*2HS was made too powerful, disrupting class balance.  Knights with high-end 2HS outdamage dual-wielders with high-end 1H weapons (esp on high AC MOBs).<br>
*Lack of high-end ranger weapons (RNG weapons are proportionally inferior to war/rog/mnk/knight weaponary when compared to Kunark or Velious) <p>Locz Agneyastra <BR>
